text: Eupterote celebica is a moth in the family Eupterotidae. It was described by Wolfgang A. Nässig, Jeremy Daniel Holloway and Martin Beeke in 2011. It is found in Sulawesi, Indonesia. The length of the forewings is 37–40 mm for males and 51 mm for females. Adults have a variable wing pattern, ranging from yellowish to brownish., & (2011). "Description of a new species of Eupterote (Eupterote) from Sulawesi (Indonesia) (Lepidoptera: Eupterotidae)". Nachrichten des Entomologischen Vereins Apollo.
